  "paragraphs": [
    {
      "para_id": "Q001093.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(i 1) For Ninĝirsu , Enlil’s warrior ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001093.3",
      "line_range": "3",
      "translation": "(i 3) En-metena , ruler of Lagaš , child of En-ana-tum , ruler of Lagaš , descendant of Ur-Nanše , king of Lagaš , built the sanctuary of Dugru for Ninĝirsu . He built the Ahuš , the temple that is looked upon with favour , for him ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001093.19",
      "line_range": "19",
      "translation": "(iii 5) For Lugal-Uruba , he built his great temple in Urub ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001093.22",
      "line_range": "22",
      "translation": "(iv 2) For Nanše , he built the E-engur in Zulum ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001093.25",
      "line_range": "25",
      "translation": "(iv 5) For Enki , king of Eridug , he built the Abzu-pasira ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001093.29",
      "line_range": "29",
      "translation": "(v 2) For Ninhursaĝa , he built the high temple of Tirkug ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001093.33",
      "line_range": "33",
      "translation": "(v 6) For Ninĝirsu , he built the Antasura , the temple whose fearsome radiance covers all the lands ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001093.37",
      "line_range": "37",
      "translation": "(vi 4) For Enlil , he built the E-adda in Imsaĝ ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001093.40",
      "line_range": "40",
      "translation": "(vi 8) He built the temple of Ĝatumdug ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001093.41",
      "line_range": "41",
      "translation": "(vii 1) For Nanše , he built the Šage-pada . For Nanše , he built her lofty high temple ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001093.47",
      "line_range": "47",
      "translation": "(vii 7) At that time , En-metena built his brewery for Ninĝirsu , his master who loves him ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001093.52",
      "line_range": "52",
      "translation": "(viii 5) The personal god of En-metena , the builder of Ninĝirsu’s brewery , is Šul-MUŠxPA ."
    }
  ],
